.TH TRACER 1 "March 2026" "tracer" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tracer \- browse, inspect, resume, and delete Claude Code sessions
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tracer
.RB [ \-v | \-\-version ]
.br
.B tracer update
.br
.B tracer theme
.RB [ name ]
.br
.B tracer man
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B tracer
is an interactive TUI for managing Claude Code sessions stored in
.IR ~/.claude/ .
It displays all past sessions in a navigable table with name, date,
working directory, and git branch. Sessions can be filtered, inspected,
resumed, copied, pinned, or deleted.
.PP
Session names respect the
.B /rename
command from Claude Code. If a session was renamed, the custom name is shown
instead of the first user message.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B update
Check for the latest release on GitHub and update the binary in place.
Falls back to
.B sudo
if the install path is not writable.
.TP
.B theme \fR[\fIname\fR]
Without arguments, opens an interactive theme picker with live preview.
With a name argument, sets the theme directly.
Run \fBtracer theme\fR to see all available themes and preview them interactively.
.TP
.B man
View this manual page.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-version
Print the version and exit.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a short help message and exit.
.SH KEY BINDINGS
.SS List View
.TS
l l.
Key	Action
_
Enter	Resume session
v	View session details
c	Copy session ID to clipboard
p	Pin/unpin session to top
d	Delete session
s	Open settings
/	Filter sessions
Esc	Clear filter
\(ua/\(da	Navigate
q	Quit
.TE
.SS Detail View
.TS
l l.
Key	Action
_
Enter	Resume session
c	Copy session ID to clipboard
d	Delete session
\(ua/\(da	Scroll conversation
Esc	Back to list
.TE
.SS Settings View
.TS
l l.
Key	Action
_
\(ua/\(da	Navigate settings
\(<-/\(->	Change value
Enter	Change value
Esc	Save and go back
.TE
.SH SETTINGS
Accessible via the
.B s
key from the list view, or by editing
.IR ~/.config/tracer/config.json .
.TP
.B Theme
Color theme (default, minimal, ocean, rose).
.TP
.B Sort by
Default sort order: date (newest first), name (alphabetical), or directory.
.TP
.B Show date
Toggle the Date column in the list view.
.TP
.B Show directory
Toggle the Directory column in the list view.
.TP
.B Show branch
Toggle the Branch column in the list view.
.TP
.B Confirm delete
When on, deleting a session requires a y/N confirmation.
When off, sessions are deleted immediately.
.SH DETAIL VIEW
The detail view shows session metadata including:
.IP \(bu 2
Session ID, date, working directory, git branch
.IP \(bu 2
Message count (user and assistant)
.IP \(bu 2
Context usage progress bar (tokens used vs. model context window)
.IP \(bu 2
Output token count
.IP \(bu 2
Scrollable conversation preview
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.claude/projects/{path}/{sessionId}.jsonl
Session conversation files. Each JSONL line is a message entry.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/history.jsonl
Global history log. Used to detect /rename commands.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/file\-history/{sessionId}/
File version history per session. Deleted when a session is removed.
.TP
.I ~/.claude/tasks/{sessionId}/
Task definitions per session. Deleted when a session is removed.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tracer/config.json
Persistent settings (theme, sort order, column visibility, confirm delete).
.TP
.I ~/.config/tracer/pins.json
Pinned session IDs.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate the
.I ~/.claude/
directory and to shorten paths in the display.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Normal exit.
.TP
.B 1
Error (failed to scan sessions, update failure, etc.)
.SH EXAMPLES
Launch the TUI:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer
.RE
.PP
Check current version:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer \-\-version
.RE
.PP
Update to the latest release:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer update
.RE
.PP
Open interactive theme picker:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer theme
.RE
.PP
Set theme directly:
.PP
.RS
.B tracer theme ocean
.RE
